The truth. Novak Djokovic entered Australia with the support of Tennis Australia and a medical exemption from the state of Victoria but he entered Australia with out meeting the listed exemption requirements of the Australian Federal Government - his visa application is to the Australian Government  (Federal law in Australia overrides state laws)- When Novak Djokovic entered via Melbourne airport the visa was questioned as his exemption status. Having not met the Federal exemption status for covid like any other traveler his visa was cancelled and placed in a detention facility. No exception are made if a person is famous rich etc all go through the same process. 

When the border protection services (who vet visa holders on arrival) questioned Novak Djokovicthe on arrival and asked for medical evidence under federal exemption status he didn't meet the criteria. The border agency then requested the Victorian state government to support Novak Djokovic exemption status - they refused. Tennis Australia is at fault for not adhering to Australian Federal criteria for covid exemptions and instead relied on state covid requirements leading to this event. The state of Victoria entry requirements is mainly created for domestic interstate travelers and the state own requirements for overseas travelers - but the Victorian law cannot over ride federal law.  I am sure Novak Djokovic will now be deported and as such banned from Australia for the next three years 

Plus this deportation will affect his ability to successfully acquire future visa's from other countries for the rest of his life, because he has been deported by the Australian government and maybe placed on a not entry list.

snippet.textDisplay:
As context, the Serbian government requires any traveller from Australia to be vaccinated to enter their country in the exact same manner that Novak Djokovic sought to enter Australia. The Australian public is on the whole extremely angry that celebrities like ‘tennis stars’ are expecting special treatment merely on the basis of their celebrity status.
What kind of ‘medical condition’ would a high ranking tennis player genuinely have to enable him to enter Australia without a vaccination? His documentation was deemed insufficient by the federal government when he tried to arrive. To qualify for an exemption, it is clearly stipulated that the person entering must either have caught Covid in the last 6 months, or been diagnosed with a *specific* medical disorder (from a very limited list of medical conditions) that causes a severe reaction to AZ or an mrna vaccine. Novak met neither condition.

Medical resources are being stretched to their limit in Australia, which is why we require vaccination for those entering the country. You have to respect that Australia is a highly vaccinated country, with little tolerance for ‘celebrities’ who expect special treatment. Many Australians have struggled to return home over the past 2 years, and some have missed the deaths and funerals of loved ones.
